  "text": "Previous research has noted that registers are idle for many cycles after their last use, before being placed on the free-list to be assigned to a new instruction [CITATION_1] . This is because a register cannot be released until the instruction redefining its logical register commits, in order to maintain a precise processor state in the event of an exception, interrupt or branch mis-prediction occurring.",
